    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="770"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/837a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Odessa</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RJA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-12T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 12, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Please report immediately conditions your district as affecting army, food
                    supplies, sentiment for separate peace. What information have you regarding
                    progress of reported effort by <persName corresp="#p_AGMV1"
                        >Alexeev</persName>,<note n="1" xml:id="d770fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_AGMV1">Gen. M. V. Alexeev</persName>, from March to
                        June 1917 Commander in Chief of the Russian Army and in September 1917 Chief
                        of Staff; at this time engaged with <persName corresp="#p_KLG1"
                            >Kornilov</persName> and others in the formation of the Volunteer
                        Army.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KLG1">Kornilov</persName>,<note n="2" xml:id="d770fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KLG1">Gen. L. G. Kornilov</persName>, in July 1917
                        commander of the southwestern front and from July to September 1917
                        Commander in Chief of the Russian Army.</note> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_KGAM1">Kaledin</persName>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d770fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KGAM1">Gen. A.M. Kaledin</persName>, Ataman of the Don
                        Cossacks.</note> to reconstruct loyal portions of army.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
